br>mukodik, hogy mindket felet versenyeztetve, kivarva szerzi meg <br>maganak a legnagyobb hatalmat az, aki AUTONOM POLITIKAI ERO. <br>Az orosz "patyomkin-demokracia" -eppen ugy mint a magyar- <br>csupan satnya kulissza azonban, ami mogott massziv <br>hatalomatmentes folyik. A 90-es es 94-es "demokratikus" <br>valasztasok nalunk is eppen ilyen ures kirakatrendezesek voltak!]<br><br>2. Gazdasag<br><br>[Azt "hoznak ki", amit akarnak, elszamolasi zsonglorkodessel, hiszen <br>elszamoltatas es elszamolas NINCS!]<br><br>A hazankba erkezo mukodotoke - a statisztikai elszamolasi rendszer <br>miatt - rontja a Magyar Nemzeti Bank teljesitmenyet, es igy noveli az <br>allamhaztartasi deficitet. Mas kerdes, hogy jovore valoszinuleg <br>nyereseges lehet a jegybank, hiszen a nem kamatozo adossag <br>atalakitasaval tobb mint 100 miliardot kap pluszban kamatkent a <br>koltsegvetestol. Ez nincs hatassal az allamhaztartas egyenlegere - <br>mondotta a NSZV-nak Tetenyi Tamas, a PM helyettes allamtitkara.<br><br>[A liberalbolsevik "ujsagiras" tovabbi talanyai, a 26 orszag kozul<br>UTOLSO HARMADIK helyezesunk "kozmetikazasara"]<br><br>Az OECD szerint Magyarorszagon az iden ketto, jovore pedig harom <br>szazalekos gazdasagi novekedes varhato. Az evente ketszer keszitett <br>OECD-prognozisok soraban most eloszor szerepelt a tagok kozott <br>Magyarorszag. Az 1994-es adatok alapjan a 41,4 milliard dollaros <br>GDP a 24. helyet kapta. Az osszehasonlitasban csak 26 orszag <br>szerepel, mert a masik uj tagot, Csehorszagot nem vettek meg <br>figyelembe. A jelentes szerint az egy fore juto brutto hazai termek <br>Magyarorszagon eleg alacsony, korulbelul 4000 dollar - am a vasarlo <br>ero eltereset is szamitasba veve az ertek 6300 dollar. A prognozis <br>szerint a vartnal lassaban novekszik a fejlett orszagok gazdasaga <br>(NSZV). [Hogy lett a mi $4,000-unkbol $6,300? Ha a skalat <br>individualisan atirjuk, az egesz 26 orszagos besorolasnak semmi <br>ertelme. Kit neznek ezek hulyenek?]<br><br>[Negyedev alatt majdnem 10%-al zuhant a realber. Egy ev alatt tehat <br>a berek elvesztik EGYHARMADUKAT. Johet a "sikerpropaganda"]<br><br>Hazankban a munkavallalok letukert kuzdenek, az allampolgarok <br>tobbsegenek a megelhetese forog veszelyben. A mult esztendo <br>sokkolo megszoritasai utan a kormany kotelezettseget vallalt ugyan, <br>hogy az idei realbercsokkenes merteke nem haladja meg a 2 <br>szazalekot, azonban az elso negyedevi 9,5 szazalek mar most <br>bizonyossa teszi, hogy az igeret tarthatatlan. A terhek elsosorban az <br>egyebkent is elesett, am erdekei ervenyesitesere kevesse kepes <br>retegeket sujtja. A szakszervezetek targyalasos alkura keszulnek, am <br>megoszottak. Az MSZOSZ a kovetkezo ket evre ar-bermegallapodast <br>javasol, mig az autonomok nem tamogatjak ezt az allaspontot. <br>Hatarozottan kiallnak azert, hogy ebben az evben - a kormany es a <br>szakszervezetek megallapodasanak megfeleloen - legfeljebb 2 <br>szazalekos lehet a realbercsokkenes. Szerintuk a kormany arra <br>jatszik, hogy a valasztasok kozeledtevel kulonbozo - a jovo evben <br>ervenybe lepo - adokedvezmenyekkel szelesitse szavazobazisat. <br>Ennek arat azonban ket-harom ev mulva a munkavallaloknak <br>kellene megfizetniuk, megpedig jelentos realbercsokkenessel (UM).<br><br>1. Belpolitika<br><br>[Mint pufjkas, megoltem szabadsagharcosokat 56-ban. Most pedig <br>loptam szazmillio forintot.  Na es?]<br><br>Szazmillio forintot er a budai Horn-villa. <br>(Lovas Istvan ujsagiro informacioi alapjan) <br>[Teljes szoveg: megjelent: Uj Magyarorszag, junius 20]<br><br>Hivatalos ingatlanszakertoi velemenyek szerint legalabb 100-120 <br>millio forintot er az az ingatlan, amelyet "Horn Gyula es tarsai" <br>jelzessel tartanak nyilvan a Fovarosi Keruletek Foldhivatalanal. <br>Lapunk informacioi szerint a III. kerulet, Remetehegyi ut 178 szam <br>alatti villatelekhez a Postabank Invest reven jutott hozza a <br>kormanyfo - kedvezmenyes aron. Csupan a telek forgalmi erteke 15-<br>20 millio forint.<br><br>Horn Gyula elozo lakasa [a lap mind a Remetehegyi villa, mind a <br>lipotvarosi berkaszarnya-lakas kulso fenykepet kozli]  a XIII. <br>kerulet, Ujpesti rakpart 11. szamu hazban volt, amely jelenleg a Dom <br>Epitoipari Reszvenytarsasag rendelkezeseben levo szolgalati lakas. Az <br>adasvetel teto ala hozasaban nagy valoszinuseggel reszt vett a mar <br>emlitett penzintezet ingatlankereskedelemben jaratos csoportja. Ezt <br>Muranyi Robert, a Postabank marketingigazgatoja kerdesunkre <br>cafolta. A penzintezet vezeto beosztasu szakembere ugyanakkor nem <br>titkolta: a lakas uj tulajdonosa a Dom Rt, amelynek szakemberei es <br>kivitelezo munkasai a Horn-villat felepitettek.<br><br>Az 1994-es parlamenti valasztasokat kovetoen a Magyar Szocialista <br>Part elso embere, magyarorszag uj miniszterelnoke elobb nemet <br>mondott, majd a biztonsagi szolgalat nyomasara szinte azonnal <br>atkoltozott a hivatalos kormanyrezidenciara, a XII. kerulet Bela <br>kiraly uti villaba.<br><br>A Lovs Istvan ujsagirotol kapott informacio szerint ezt kovetoen a <br>Horn csalad tobb mas tagjanak birtokaban levo ingatlan ertekesitese <br>utan kezdodott meg a Remetehegyi uti epitkezes.  A minegy 500 <br>negyzetmeteres villa kivitelezeset a fent emlitett szekszardi es pecsi <br>telephellyel egyarant rendelkezo Dom Rt. vallalta.  A ceg torzstokeje <br>allitolag 1.6 milliard forint, es ugy tudjuk, korulbelul 200 dolgozot <br>foglalkoztattak.  Az APEH-nel nyilvantartott alkalmazottaik <br>bejelentett brutto atlagkeresete mindossze 20-30 ezer forint kozott <br>mozog.<br><br>A Remetehegyi ut lakoinak elmondasa szerint a rovid ideig tarto <br>epitoipari tevekenyseget "kulso", azaz roman, illetve ukran <br>nemzetisegu munkaerovel is kiegeszitettek.  Egy ott dolgozo munkas <br>informacioja szerint a luxuskivitelu villa alapterulete legalabb 150-<br>160 negyzetmeter.  Az ingatlanbol a maximalis igenyeket kielegito <br>uszomedence sem hianyzik: hozzavetoleges erteke 20 millio forint <br>korul mozog.<br><br>A lakatlan haz bejaratat ejjel-nappal biztonsagi emberek orzik, akik - <br>ertelemszeruen- nem mondanak semmit a haz titkairol. Annyit <br>azonban elmondtak, hogy a lakohaz egy csaladi vallalkozas reszet <br>kepezi.  Ugyancsak a lakok elmondasa alapjan tajekozodhattunk <br>arrol, hogy a miniszterelnok sem a kivitelezes soran, sem pedig <br>annak vegeztevel nem latogatta rendszeresen a villat.  A [lap <br>fenykepen jol lathato] vasracsos ablakok alatt allo, COS 978-as <br>rendszamu Mercedes allami auto. A benne ulo gepkocsivezeto eppen <br>Horn Gyula felesegere varakozott, aki nehany csomaggal szallt be a <br>negykereku fekete csodaba.<br><br>Pazar a termesko tamfal, a rajta emelkedo oszlopok, a kozejuk <br>szoritott kerites csakugy, mint a haz udvaran az enyhe ivu kanyarral <br>epitett autofordulo.  Mindezt gondosan nyirt zold pazsit ovezi.  <br>Allitolag a kivitelezo Dom Rt. a III. kerulet szamos pontjan, igy a <br>Lajos utcaban is tobb haz felepiteseben erdekelt.  A rendkivul magas <br>ertekesitesi arak miatt azonban, ugy tudjuk, a Szerencsejatek Rt-nek <br>is ki kellett vennie a reszet a lakoteruletek megvasarlasabol.<br><br>A fenti ugylet eljarasjogi es hivatali szakszerusegeben nem <br>ketelkedve az Uj Magyarorszag megkerdezi: a sulyos gazdasagi es <br>tarsadalmi valsagokkal kuszkodo hazaban milyen fenyt vet az orszag <br>miniszterelnokere, ha korabbi valasztasi igereteit - a tenyek ezt <br>mutatjak - maga is megszegni latszik? (AsC)<br><br>[az Uj M.o. utoirata:] Megjelenes elott cikkunket atfaxoltuk Kiss <br>Elemer allamtitkarnak, kerve, hogy a miniszterelnok valaszoljon a <br>cikkben foglaltakra.  Horn Gyula szemelyi titkara, Baranyi Maria <br>kozolte, a miniszterelnok ur nem valaszol.<br><br>[Az FKGP parlamenti vizsgalatot kezdemenyez Horn Gyula palotajarol]<br><br>Az FKGP parlamenti vizsgalobizottsag letrehozasat javasolja, amely <br>elott Horn Gyula miniszterelnok szamot adhatna hazepitesenek <br>korulmenyeirol - jelentette be Torgyan Jozsef, az FKGP elnoke a part <br>tegnapi sajtotajekoztatojan. A kisgazdak hetfon megkezdik a <br>bizottsag letrehozasahoz szukseges 78 kepviseloi alairas <br>osszegyujteset. Torgyan ugy velte, a vizsgalobizottsagban a <br>miniszterelnok tisztazhatna azokat a szerintuk alaptalan ragalmakat, <br>hogy " a villa az egykori elvbaratok altal elkomunizalt tanacsi <br>lakasok eladasabol epult fel". A kisgazdak szerint a miniszterelnok <br>jelentos vagyongyarapodasa miatt szukseges lenne, ha Horn <br>vagyonnyilatkozatot tenne es nyilvanossagra is hozna. A <br>vizsgalobizottsagnak tisztaznia kell az ingatlan tulajdonjogat, az <br>epites korulmenyeit, benne azt, hogy valoban voltak-e a munkasok <br>kozt feketen dolgozo ukranok es romanok (NSZ).<br><br>[Kosane politikai halotta nyilvanitotta magat]<br><br>"A hir igaz, Horn Gyula hazat epittetett, de nem szazmilliokert [csak <br>egyszazmillioert] es nem a sajtoban kozzetett alapteruleten [hiszen <br>ott ketfele alapterulet szerepel, amibol csak egyik lehet igaz]" - <br>mondta Kosane Kovacs Magda, az MSZP ugyvezeto alelnoke egy <br>bekescsabai sajtotajekoztaton. Leszogezte: "Nagyon kellene <br>szegyellnie magat a hazamnak, ha a miniszterelnoke, amikor befejezi <br>politikai palyajat, nem lakhatna olyan korulmenyek kozott, ahol az <br>egesz csaladjaval egyutt elhet". Kosane hozzatette: mas <br>mondanivaloja nincs a dologrol, legfoljebb az, hogy hatartalan tud <br>lenni bizonyos lapok es egyes ujsagirok rosszindulata (NSZ). [Azt is <br>mondhatta volna ugyan, hogy hatartalan tud lenni egyes politikusok <br>hazugsaga, akik "szocialisan erzekeny" hatalmat igernek es azt hogy <br>meg a hivatalos miniszterelnoki rezidenciara sem koltoznek at <br>"proletar szerenysegbol", majd a FEL ORSZAGOT nyomorba dontik, <br>mig maguk szazmilliot rabolnak fenyuzo maganpalotajukra]<br><br>[Nepszabi a Horn-palotarol]<br><br>"Horn Gyula korabban eppen lapunknak nyilatkozott az epitkezesrol.<br>A tavaly decemberben adott interjujaban a kormanyfo elmondta: <br>"Lanyommal elunk, kettonk korabbi lakasanak arabol epitkezunk." <br>[Ami nyilvanvalo hazugsag]<br><br>[Magyar Hirlap a Horn-palotarol]<br><br>A Fuggetlen Kisgazdapart olyan parlamenti vizsgalobizottsag <br>felallitasat inditvanyozza, mely a Horn-villa rejtelyeire<br>deritene fenyt. Szorgalmazzak, hogy a miniszterelnok reszletesen <br>szamoljon el a bizottsag elott a villa koltsegeirol, s tegyen<br>vagyonnyilatkozatot.  Torgyan utalt a miniszterelnok beszedeire, <br>melyekben szuksegesnek itelte a vagyonnyilatkozatot, s felemelte <br>szavat a feketegazdasag ellen. A kisgazdak elso embere az Uj <br>Magyarorszagra hivatkozva megemlitette, hogy a 100-120 milliot<br>ero Horn-villa epiteseben romaniai es ukrajnai munkasok is reszt <br>vettek. Torgyan Jozsef megjegyezte: Horn Gyula volt ujlipotvarosi <br>lakasanak most az az rt. a tulajdonosa, amelynek szakemberei a <br>Horn-villat folepitettek. Az FKGP elnoke kozolte: megkezdik az <br>alairasgyujtest a vizsgalobizottsag felallitasara, s szamitanak <br>mindazokra, akiknek fontos a kozelet tisztasaga. Kosane<br>Kovacs Magda, az MSZP ugyvezeto alelnoke egy kerdesre tegnap <br>Bekescsaban kijelentette: Nagyon kellene szegyellnie magat az en <br>hazamnak, hogy miniszterelnoke, ha egyszer befejezi politikai <br>palyajat, ne lakhasson olyan korulmenyek kozott, ahol az egesz <br>csaladjaval egyutt elhet - idezte az MTI Kosanet. A miniszterelnok <br>epitkezesevel kapcsolatban az Uj Magyarorszagban megjelent iras<br>tobb ellenorizetlen felinformaciot es tudatos csusztatast tartalmaz, <br>ezert arra Horn Gyula nem kivan reagalni - jelentette ki kerdesunkre <br>Szabo Jozsef Jeno, a kormanyfo sajtotitkara. Szerinte kerdeses<br>peldaul az, hogy a meg nem nevezett szomszedok altal elmondottak <br>mennyire tekinthetok hitelesnek. Ha az epitkezesen valoban <br>alkalmaztak kulfoldieket, azert is inkabb a kivitelezo, mint a <br>megrendelo felel. Szabo ugy velekedett, hogy a Postabank<br>Investnek a telekvasarlasban betoltott szerepet a cikk nem tisztazza, <br>mikent azt sem, miert kellett a Szerencsejatek Rt.-nek reszt vennie <br>bizonyos ingatlanugyletekben. Egyebkent az, hogy a miniszterelnok <br>csaladjaval kozosen hazat epittet Obudan, mar korabban is <br>nyilvanossagra kerult, vagyis azt senki sem igyekezett titkolni -<br>mondta a sajtotitkar.  Az epuletet kivitelezo Dom Epitoipari Rt.<br>igazgatosagi elnoke, dr. Szogesdi Judit kozolte: az "ugyben nem erzik <br>erintve magukat", es semmilyen formaban nem kivannak reagalni a <br>Remetehegyi uti epitkezessel kapcsolatos cikkekre. Ertesuleseink <br>szerint az ingatlan tulajdonjoga meg nincs bejegyezve, a szeljegyzet <br>formajaban jelzett kerelmet pedig meg nem biralta el a Fovarosi <br>Keruletek  Foldhivatala. Tarlos Istvan obudai polgarmester <br>kerdesunkre kozolte: nem tud arrol, hogy barki is kulonleges <br>elbanast kert volna az onkormanyzattol a hatosagi engedelyek <br>beszerzesekor. A telek nem az onkormanyzat tulajdona, a szokasos <br>hatosagi eljarason kivul nem erintettek a kerdesben - mondta Tarlos.<br>Ingatlanszakertok szerint a III. keruleti Remetehegyi uton a <br>telekarak fekvestol fuggoen tiz es tizenotezer forint kozott<br>mozognak negyzetmeterenkent. [Ilyen esetekben, amikor vitatott <br>tenyek szerepelnek nagyjelentosegu kozeleti dolgokban, egyetlen <br>normalis demokratikus eljaras a TELJES ES NYILT KIVIZSGALAS!]<br><br>[Horn nagyot alkotott palotajaval: letrejott az ellenzek egysege]<br><br>Politikusok - Giczy Gyorgy, Lezsak Sandor, Csurka Istvan, Torgyan <br>Jozsef es Thurmer Gyula egyarant eliteloen nyilatkoznak a <br>kormanyfo lakasepiteserol. Czako Gabor iro leszogezte: "Ma Horn <br>Gyula a legnagyobb ideologus, hiszen a magyar ideologiat ket szoval <br>megalkotta: na es! A magyar nep ezt elfogadta, nagyon helyeslem, <br>hogy ezek utan a miniszterelnok megtestesiti azt a szemleletet, amit <br>elvarnak tole. Elvegre amikor 56-rol es pufajkas multjarol kerdeztek, <br>akkor mindossze ezt a bizonyos na es?-t reagalta a feltett kerdesre es <br>ez elegendo volt ahhoz, hogy megvalasszak. Azt nem tudom, hogy ez <br>a fajta ideologia europainak nevezheto-e, mindenesetre az teny, hogy <br>a mai magyar kozvelemeny ezt akarja, ezt varja el tole" (UM).<br><br>[Minden a kleptokracia szabalyai szerint tortent]<br><br>Ifjabb Horn Gyula kozolte: barmilyen vizsgalatnak nyugodtan neznek <br>elebe, minden torvenyes es szabalyos volt. A kormanyfo semmilyen <br>modon nem kivant reagalni az ugyre (NSZV). Az Uj Magyarorszag <br>fenykepet kozol Szekeres Imre, az MSZP frakciovezetojenek budai <br>villajarol, amely a lap szerint nem torpul el a miniszterelnoke <br>mellett. (Valami jo uzletember rajohetne, hogy bestseller fotoalbumot <br>lehetne kesziteni a "Kleptokrata Palotakrol")<br><br>[Aki legvarat epit, ne sajnalja a teglat!]<br><br>A kormany tegnapi ulesen jovahagyta az orszag husz evre szolo <br>modernizacios programjat, amely alaptetelnek tekinti, hogy hazank <br>az EU es a NATO lesz [Jo mi? Felepitenek egy huszeves tervet olyan <br>ket alaptetelre, melynek egyike sem igaz, sot kevesse valoszinu hogy <br>valaha is igaz lesz!] . A kabinet elso olvasatban, a konkret <br>keretszamok elfogadasa nelkul targyalt a jovo evi koltsegvetes <br>iranyelveirol. Ertesulesek szerint jovore 18 szazalekos inflacioval, a <br>fizetesi merleg 1,5 millio dollaros hianyaval szamol, es azzal, hogy <br>jovore 22 ezer allashely szunik meg, a kozponti koltsegvetesi <br>szferaban, es 20 ezer az onkormanyzatok kozalkalmazottainal. A <br>kormany ugy dontott, hogy nem tamogatja a 10 ezer korhazi agy idei <br>leepitesenek folyamatat idoben elhalaszto modosito javaslatok <br>parlamenti elfogadasat. Mint ismeretes, tobb MSZP-s kepviselo <br>javasolta, hogy a leepitest a leginkabb erintett  regiokban a jovo ev <br>junius vegeig lehessen vegrehajtani (NSZ, NM).<br><br>[Fustado, lelegzetveteli dij, adoado kovetkezik]<br><br>Ismet felvetettek a vizitdij bevezeteset a penzugyi tarca <br>szakemberei, am a Nepjoleti Miniszterium ellenzi, hogy <br>teriteskotelesse tegyenek egyes egeszsegugyi ellatasokat. <br>Ugyanakkor a tarcanal keszulo biztositasi torveny a mai tb-jarulek <br>helyett mar tarsadalombiztositasi adoval szamol, amelyet <br>mindenkire, meg az eltartottakra is kivetnenek (NSZV).<br><br>[Zelnik harmincmilliot sikkasztott - na es? Ekkora osszeggel <br>legfeljebb a "futottak meg" kategoriaba kerulhet bele]<br><br>A MH birtokaba kerult dokumentumokbol kiderult, hogy a Muveszeti <br>es Szabadmuvelodesi Alapitvany tobb mint 30 millios vesztesege <br>mogott egyebek mellett egy olyan penzatutalas all, amelynek <br>kereteben Zelnik Jozsef, a kuratorium elnoke kozpenzeket utalt at <br>sajat Kulturalis Innovacios Alapitvanya szamlajara. A lap megjegyzi: <br>Zelnik, aki tarstulajdonosa a Kulturalis Informacios Vallalatnak, az <br>Orszagos Radio es Televizio Testulet KDNP altal delegalt tagja.<br><br>[Lezsak az MDF tarsadalmi bazisanak kiterjeszteset probalja]<br><br>Lezsak Sandor az MDF tegnapi tajekoztatojan elmondta, hogy partja <br>nem utasitja el a partingatlanok tulajdoni helyzetet rendezo <br>torvenyjavaslat legujabb valtozatat, am annak alairasa elott meg <br>szuksegesnek tartja a tovabbi egyeztetest. A partelnok nem tartja <br>kizartnak, hogy a torvenyjavaslatot meg a parlament nyari szunete <br>elott benyujtja az MSZP, az SZDSZ, a KDNP, valamint az MDF. Lezsak <br>Sandor bejelentette, hogy letrehozzak az MDF munkas-, vallalkozoi-, <br>nyugdijas-es falutagozatat. Celjuk, hogy a tarsadalom valamennyi <br>retegevel legyen kapcsolata az MDF-nek, csakugy, mint 1990 elott, <br>masreszt igyekeznek megoldani azokat a problemakat, amelyeket a <br>jelenlegi kormany valasztasi igeretei ellenere nem oldott meg (MG).<br><br>[Kisvarda kilepett az SZDSZ-bol. Hogy is van az a mondas a sullyedo <br>hajorol valo menekulesrol?]<br><br>Kilepett az SZDSZ-bol a part kisvardai szervezete. Ennek oka, hogy <br>Kisvarda polgarmesteret, Olah Albertet az SZDSZ Szabolcs-Szatmar-<br>Bereg Megyei egyeztetotanacsa - szerintuk igazsagtalanul - kizarta a <br>partbol. A dontest a testulet azzal indokolta, hogy Olah Albert <br>kilepett a megyei kozgyules SZDSZ-frakciojabol. A kisvardai szervezet <br>a kilepest bejelento nyilatkozataban megdobbeneset fejezi ki, hogy az <br>SZDSZ egyik ismert, tobb valasztast is megnyert szemelyiseget a <br>partbol kizartak, s errol a sajtobol kellett ertesulnie. A dokumentrum <br>leszogezi: "Nem vagyunk hajlandoak kiszolgalni partunk eredmenyei <br>altal ervenyesulni akaro, hozzank karriervagybol es anyagi <br>erdekekbol csatlakozo egyenek torekveseit". Az UM-ban Olah Albert <br>elmondta, hogy nemzeti-liberalis beallitottsagu, es ez valoszinuleg <br>nem tetszett egyes SZDSZ-es politikusoknak.<br><br>[Az SZDSZ csak olyan valasztasba meg bele, melynek eredmenyet <br>elore meghatarozza]<br><br>Az Orszaggyules csutortokon lezarta az uj alkotmany koncepciojanak <br>reszletes vitajat. Hat part tamogatja a azt a javaslatot, hogy a <br>kulfoldon elo magyar allampolgarok is kapjanak valasztojogot, az <br>SZDSZ kepviseloje azonban ugy velte, annak elfogadasa <br>"belathatatlan" kovetkezmenyekkel jarna (MH). [A magyar <br>"patyomkin-demokrataknak" meg arrol sincs fogalmuk, hogy <br>allampolgarok -barhol is legyenek- a valasztojogot nem "KAPJAK", <br>hanem az nekik VAN - legfeljebb fasiszta-kommunista diktaturak ezt <br>az alapjogot nem ismerik el. Sikerult azonban osszehozni az SZDSZ-<br>nek, hogy az emigracionak egyedul az SZDSZ-el kell szembenallnia!]<br><br>[Meg sokaig kell fontolgatni, hogy kirepultek-e, es hogy ami napnal <br>nyilvanvalobban alkotmanyellenes, annak tagadasaval <br>kiserletezzenek-e?]<br><br>Az elozetes varakozasoktol elteroen nem keszult el csutortokon a <br>parlament honvedelmi bizottsaganak jelentese, amely a MiG-29-es <br>repulok lengyelorszagi gyakorlata miatt inditott vizsgalatot zarta <br>volna le. A testulet a tegnapi ulesen ugy hatarozott, hogy julius 3-ig <br>kesziti el jelenteset (NSZ).<br><br>[Olaszorszagbol jol latszik a Kleptokracia, az Egyhazzal valo packazas, <br>de az Egyhazugyi Hivatal hivatasos hazudozoja, Ugyeletes Ivan<br>persze sem nem lat, se nem hall]<br><br>Az olasz Avvenire cimu katolikus lap azt allitotta, hogy a magyar <br>katolikus egyhazi vezetes idonyerest szolgalo kibuvonak iteli Horn <br>Gyula javaslatat az ingatlanrendezesi torveny modositasarol. Az <br>egyhazi kapcsolatokert felelos allamtitkar, Platthy Ivan cafolja ezt az <br>allitast. Gyulay Endre, a katolikus puspoki kar alelnoke viszont <br>elmondta: az utobbi ket evben a kormany es a vallasi vezetok szobeli <br>egyezkedesein kivul alig tortent valami erdemleges az egyhazi <br>ingatlanok tulajdonrendezesenek eloremozditasa ugyeben (MH).<br><br>[Cel a csokkenes]<br><br>Minden torvenyes eszkozzel hajlando fellepni az MSZOSZ tagsaga, ha a <br>parlament vegul a kormany elkepzelesei szerint emeli fel a nyugdij <br>korhatarat - dontott tegnap heves vita utan a szervezet szovetsegi <br>tanacsa. Tamogatja viszont az MSZOSZ a nyugdijbiztosito <br>korhataremelesre vonatkozo modosito javaslatait. Az MSZOSZ a  <br>penzugyi tarca altal javasolt uj nyugdijrendszert is ellenzi, <br>bevezetese ellen mindent megtesz majd. Augusztusban uj <br>bertargyalasokat akar a szervezet, mert ma a fizetesek kilenc <br>szazalekkal ernek kevesebbet, mint korabban, szemben az ET-ben <br>megkotott ket szazalekkal. A cel, hogy a varhatoan 26-28 szazalekos <br>inflaciotol legfeljebb ket szazalekkal elmarado beremelest ajanljon az <br>ET az ervenyben levo 19,5 szazalekos emeles helyett (MH).<br><br>[Csalas, sikkasztas, rablas, minden vonalon]<br><br>Tudatos torvenysertest allapit meg az Allami Szamvevoszek tegnap <br>nyilvanossagra hozott jelentese az Egeszsegbiztositasi Onkormanyzat <br>kockazatkezelo palyazata kapcsan. Bar az ASZ mar korabban jelezte, <br>hogy a tb csak mukodesi koltsegeket fedezhet, a kuratoriumok <br>fejlesztesre, epitkezesre, gepkocsi-es anyagbeszerzesre is ad <br>tamogatast. A nagyvonaluan megszabott kovetelmenyeket sem <br>kertek szamon, az objektiv biralati felteteleket nem ritkan a palyazo <br>ismertsege, kapcsolatrendszere potolta. Ez etikai kerdeseket is felvet <br>(MN).<br><br>[VICO minden botranyt tulel -- amig a Kleptokratak vannak uralmon]<br><br>A Fovarosi Birosag elso fokon megszuntette a Szikra Lapnyomda altal <br>a Vico Press Rt. ellen inditott felszamolasi eljarast. A Vico jogi <br>kepviselojenek tajekoztatasa szerint a birosag a felszamolasi <br>kerelmet nem talalta megalapozottnak, mert a ceg <br>fizeteskeptelensege nem volt megallapithato. A nyomda iden <br>marciusban kezdemenyezett eljarast a lapkiado ellen, mert a Vico <br>meg elismert, tobb tizmillios tartozasat sem egyenlitette ki evek ota <br>(MH).<br><br>[Munkaban Tamas Gaspar Miklos Kristallnacht-pufajkasai]<br><br>Ismeretlen tettesek betortek a Magyar Forum Raday utcai <br>szerkesztosegebe, feldultak a helyisegeket, elloptak az ujsag <br>faxkeszuleket, valamint az ott talalt nemi keszpenzt. Mivel nem ez az <br>elso eset, hogy betornek a jobboldali lap szerkesztosegebe, sot <br>elofordult, hogy a kiado emblemajat viselo kisbuszt, valamint Csurka <br>Istvan MIEP-elnok autojat is megrongaltak, Ludwig Emil foszerkeszto <br>emlekeztet Tamas Gaspar Miklos SZDSZ-es politikus nemregiben tett <br>felelotlen kijelentesere, amelyben a nemzeti oldal - kozte a Magyar <br>Forum - elleni eroszakos akciokra uszitott, a jelek szerint sikerrel <br>(UM).<br><br>==<br><br><br>==<br><br>NYILT LEVEL A KULTUSZMINISZTERHEZ [megjelent a <br>"Magyarorszagert", V-ik evf. 10. szamaban]<br><br>1996. Majus 28. <br><br>Tisztelt Miniszter Ur,<br><br>Ezt a szot, hogy "Miniszter Ur" furcsa szajizzel irom, mert nagyon <br>nehez szamomra ezt a titulust hasznalni, miutan a kormany <br>Esterhazy Petert es Petri Gyorgyot az On egyetertesevel Kossuth Dijjal <br>tuntette ki, es meg Torgyan Jozsefet is megfenyegetve <br>kepviselotarsait is megprobalta meggyozni, hogy a Kossuth Dij <br>kituntetes helyes volt, a fent emlitett szemelyek azt megerdemeltek.  <br>Tovabba On azzal indokolja ezt a cselekedetet, hogy ezek a szemelyek <br>"irok" es "kulfoldon is nagy elismeresben reszesulnek".<br><br>Ha On ezt oszinten gondolja, akkor en hiszem es tudom, hogy On nincs <br>tajekoztatva a kulfoldon elo magyarok hazaszereteterol, vagy pedig <br>On meg sohasem jart kulfoldon elo magyarok kozott. [Szerk: az is <br>lehetseges, hogy csak egy olyan kulfoldi orszagban jart "Magyar" <br>Balint, ahol sok-sok magyarorszagi szarmazasu gyulolettol telve <br>beszel szuloorszagarol!]<br><br>[...] Vorosmarty "Honszeretet" c. verse inspiralt, hogy vegyek tollat a <br>kezembe es Onnek levelet irjak:<br><br>"De el ne szenvedd, el ne turd Vered gyalazatat..."<br><br>Petri Gyorgy aljas es szennyes szavakkal emlegeti a Magyarok <br>Istenet az Apokrif cimu "koltemenyeben" es ezert Kossuth Dijjal lett <br>kituntetve?  Ez szamomra hihetetlen. Mi tortenik a hazankban? Hova <br>lett a magyar becsulet? Az Istenszeretet? Vagy talan beteljesul[t] <br>Berzsenyi Daniel "A Magyarokhoz c. versenek elso sora:<br><br>"Romlasnak indult hajdan eros Magyar..."<br><br>[...]  Ezeket nem kituntetni kellene, hanem letagadni, hogy ilyen fajta <br>egyenek is leteznek orszagunkban.  Ezeket nevezte Petofi "Sehonnai <br>bitang embereknek". [...]  Hogy kerulhetnek Spiro Gyorgy magyart <br>megszegyenito szavai szinpadjainkra, oda ahol szazadokon keresztul <br>Istent, Hazat, es magyar hosoket tisztelo szavak csengtek? Hogy <br>lehet, hogy Kossuth szent nevevel ilyen fajta szemelyeket dicsoitunk? <br>[...]<br><br>1996 marcius 15-en mi itt kulfoldon elo magyarok, magyar kokarda <br>a mellunkon, magyar zaszlo a kezunkben osszejottunk, hogy <br>megemlekezzunk 1848-rol. Meleg szivvel, konnyes szemmel <br>enekeltuk el gyonyoru himnuszunkat.  Beszedeinkben <br>megemlekeztunk Kossuth-rol es hoseinkrol.  Imadkoztunk a <br>Magyarok Istenehez, hogy segitse meg kis orszagunkat, valamint <br>magyar testvereinket akik odahaza es a nagyvilagban elnek.  Ez ido <br>alatt Onok Magyarorszagon Kossuth dij kituntetest adnak azoknak, <br>akik azt az Istent, akihez mi imadkozunk, aljas szavakkal emlegetik.  <br>Akik kicsufoljak a magyart akikert mi imadkozunk.  1956-ban a <br>zaszlonkbol kiteptuk a sarlo-kalapacsot, mert az oseinkre nezve <br>szegyen volt!  Szegyen volt, hogy az Istentol aldott szent koronank <br>helyere tettek a szovjet pecsetet.<br><br>A Magyar [?] Kormany es On ugyanugy megszegyenitette az 1848-as <br>szabadsagharc emleknapjat, mint a sarlo es kalapacs a zaszlonkat. [...]<br><br>Biztos vagyok benne, hogy levelem tartalmat a kulfoldi es az otthoni <br>magyarsag legnagyobb resze helyesli.  A magam reszerol imadkozni <br>fogok Onert es remelen, hogy radobbenve tevelygeseire, bocsanatot <br>kerve honfitarsaitol (a kormany neveben is) a kultuszminiszteriumi <br>tarcat - amely egy orszag eleteben a legkenyesebb es az egyik <br>legfontosabb a jovo tarsadalma szempontjabol, atadja egy <br>tisztesseges igaz magyar embernek, aki becsulettel es hozzaertessel <br>fogja kezelni, es nem politikai futballnak fogja hasznalni [a Szerkeszto <br>itt kenytelen egy tovabbi magyar versbol idezni: "ebredj almaidbol <br>ozvegy Pokaine.." - de ugy latszik ez a nyilt level irojanak is felotlott, <br>mert igy folytatja]:<br><br>Velemenyem szerint nem veletlen, hogy eloszor Fodor Gabort es most <br>ont tettek a kultuszminiszteri barsonyszekbe.  Csak a vak nem veszi <br>eszre az osszefuggest az Onok kinevezese es a kormany altalanos <br>nemzetzulleszto politikaja kozott, melynek legeklatansabb peldaja <br>eppen ez a kituntetesi botrany [...]<br><br>Juhasz Ferenc, <br>a "Sons & Daughters of Hungary" elnoke,  <br>AMOSZ Igazgatosagi Tag<br><br>==<br><br>REGIONALIS HIREK<br><br>[Majd ha folrobban, a magantulaj -kulfoldi persze- igy szol <br>Bermudabol: "szorri vagyok, de fizetni sem tudok, mert a cegem <br>csodot jelentett"]<br><br>HUNGARY PREPARES SECOND PLAN TO PRIVATIZE NUCLEAR POWER <br>PLANT. The passage last week of a nuclear energy law has paved the <br>way for a new privatization tender to be announced in October for <br>the Paks nuclear power plant, Magyar Hirlap reported on 21 June, <br>citing top officials. The Soviet-built nuclear plant supplies half of the <br>country's electricity, and experts believe it is a safer Soviet model <br>than Chornobyl. When the plant went on line in 1982, its life span <br>was estimated at 30 years. But management says that in its present <br>condition, the plant could be used for longer. It plans to extend the <br>facilities' life span by 10 to 15 years. During the privatization last <br>year of the country's energy sector, Paks was put up for sale in a <br>package with the core electricity company MVM but failed to find a <br>buyer. -- Zsofia Szilagyi  <br><br>EU WARNS BELARUS AGAINST NATIONALIZING BANKS. The EU has <br>recommended that the Belarusian government stop nationalizing the <br>country's commercial banks, Belarusian Radio reported on 20 June. <br>The EU warned that increasing the role of the state in the banking <br>system would lead to the "ineffective allocation of resources" because <br>the state would give priority to its own needs. It also noted that as <br>state banks tend to be tied to specific industries, they would continue <br>to issue credits to those industries, regardless of whether they were <br>profitable. -- Ustina Markus<br><br>NATO CONFERENCE IN WARSAW. Senior officials from more than 30 <br>countries belonging to NATO and the Partnership for Peace met in <br>Warsaw on 20 June for a four-day conference, the 13th NATO <br>Workshop. NATO Secretary- General Javier Solana, European NATO <br>forces military chief General George Joulwan, and the presidents of <br>some Central and East European countries, including Poland's <br>Aleksander Kwasniewski, are attending the conference. In his <br>opening speech, Kwasniewski said that "Central European states have <br>regained the capacity to determine their own affairs and acquired a <br>significant standing in the overall framework of European politics." <br>He added that Poland is ready to join NATO "at the earliest possible <br>date." -- Jakub Karpinski<br><br>CZECH POLITICAL UPDATE. The leaders of the three parties trying to <br>form a minority government met on 20 June for the sixth time since <br>the parliamentary elections but remained divided over the makeup <br>of the proposed cabinet, Czech media reported. The Civic Democratic <br>Party of Prime Minister-designate Vaclav Klaus, which won more <br>than twice the number of votes than the other prospective coalition <br>parties combined, insists on having a majority of ministerial posts. <br>The Christian- Democratic Union-Czechoslovak People's Party and the <br>Civic Democratic Alliance maintain that, together, they should have <br>parity with the ODS. A further meeting is scheduled for 21 June. -- <br>Steve Kettle<br><br>SLOVAK PRIME MINISTER PUSHES JUNIOR COALITION PARTNERS <br>ASIDE... Vladimir Meciar on 20 June announced that although his <br>government is "still functioning," his coalition is not, Slovak media <br>reported. While the Slovak National Party (SNS) and Association of <br>Workers of Slovakia (ZRS) have not withdrawn from the coalition <br>agreement, they have stopped adhering to it, Meciar alleged. He <br>added that the national pride of the SNS and the workers' honor of <br>the ZRS "stopped at" the insurance firm Slovenska poistovna, which <br>has been the main subject of coalition conflict (see OMRI Daily Digest, <br>11 June 1996). SNS and ZRS chairmen Jan Slota and Jan Luptak <br>denied that they violated the coalition agreement because of their <br>interest in controlling financial institutions. -- Sharon Fisher<br><br>-AND PREPARES TO FORM MINORITY GOVERNMENT. At the initiative <br>of the opposition Party of the Democratic Left (SDL), Meciar met on <br>20 June with representatives of all parliamentary parties, except the <br>ZRS, to garner support. Opposition leaders said they do not want <br>early elections and would prefer that Meciar serve his four-year <br>term and take responsibility for his policies. Meciar said he assumes <br>the majority of SNS and ZRS deputies will continue to work with the <br>HZDS, while "most opposition parties are also prepared to support a <br>minority government." He singled out the SDL, which said it might <br>support a minority government if its demands are met. Meciar said <br>none of the ministers representing the two coalition partners were <br>expected to leave the cabinet since they disagree with their parties' <br>leaderships. -- Sharon Fisher<br><br>SLOVAK PARLIAMENT APPROVES LAW ON FOUNDATIONS. The <br>Slovak parliament on 20 June reapproved a law on foundations first <br>passed in May but later vetoed by President Michal Kovac, Slovak <br>media reported. In doing so, it ignored objections from Kovac, <br>domestic non-profit organizations, and international critics. Before <br>the vote, Kovac appeared in the parliament to warn that the law is <br>not in harmony with Slovakia's obligations as an associated country <br>of the EU. The law takes effect on 1 September. -- Sharon Fisher<br><br>IMF WITHHOLDS LOAN TO ROMANIA. The IMF has announced it will <br>withhold a $70 million tranche of a stand-by credit to Romania until <br>the country's foreign exchange market has stabilized, an RFE/RL <br>correspondent reported on 20 June. An IMF spokesman was quoted <br>as saying that Bucharest will not be able to make further use of a <br>$480 million credit until it removes restrictions on the foreign-<br>currency holdings of Romanian banks. Romania's trade deficit in the <br>first four months of this year totaled $335 million, and the value of <br>the leu against foreign currencies has plunged over the past few <br>days. -- Dan Ionescu<br><br>RECORD LOW WHEAT HARVEST EXPECTED IN BULGARIA. Hristo <br>Kurzhin of the Agricultural Academy has predicted that the 1996 <br>wheat harvest will not exceed 2.2 tons per hectare, down from 4.5 <br>tons in 1991, Bulgarian and international media reported on 20 June. <br>This would be the lowest yield in 20 years and would result in an <br>even more acute grain shortage than in recent months. Kurzhin said <br>the government should consider importing wheat. The government <br>allowed wheat exports last year--when world market prices were <br>high--although grain was already in short supply. Later, it was <br>forced to release emergency supplies and import grain from <br>Romania, Serbia, and India. Two agriculture ministers have resigned <br>this year over the grain crisis. -- Stefan Krause<br><br>EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT DEMANDS NEW ALBANIAN ELECTIONS... <br>The European Parliament on 20 June demanded that Albania annul <br>the results of its disputed elections, AFP reported. The EU legislators <br>voted to suspend cooperation with Albania until "a democracy <br>worthy of the name" is instituted there. Meanwhile, OSCE Chairman <br>Flavio Cotti sent a personal envoy to Albania in the hope of restoring <br>"a minimum of confidence" in the political system there. Cotti pointed <br>out that the final OSCE report on the 26 May elections was "one of the <br>most critical we have read." -- Fabian Schmidt<br><br>-WHILE COUNCIL OF EUROPE MAY SUSPEND ALBANIA. Koha Jone on <br>20 June claimed that a majority of members of the Council of <br>Europe's parliamentary assembly want Albania's membership <br>suspended. Victor Ruffy, the council's rapporteur on Albania, is <br>quoted as writing to Socialist Party deputy leader Namik Dokle that <br>"Albania should be suspended from the Council of Europe until the <br>re-holding of new and free elections," Reuters reported. Danish <br>Foreign Minister Niels Helveg Petersen told President Sali Berisha <br>that Albania "must realize if they want to be part of us, they must <br>play by the rules, and the rules are democratic elections." Meanwhile, <br>the Albanian Central Election Commission has accused some OSCE <br>observers of collaborating with late dictator Enver Hoxha. Similar <br>earlier allegations in the daily Albania have been dismissed by <br>diplomats close to the OSCE as "completely unfounded." -- Fabian <br>Schmidt<br><br>[Na, most megtudjuk, miert nem tetszik az uj Alban rendszer:]<br><br>SIX ALBANIAN COMMUNIST-ERA OFFICIAL SENTENCED TO LIFE <br>IMPRISONMENT. Former communist chief ideologue Foto Cami, <br>Defense Minister Prokop Murra, and Politburo member Muho Asllani <br>have been sentenced to life imprisonment. Former communist party <br>First-Secretary Gaqo Nesho, Tirana police chief Dilaver Bengasi, and <br>secret police chief Zef Loka were jailed for 16, 18, and 20 years <br>respectively. The court found them guilty of crimes against <br>humanity, including deportations of up to 500 people, AFP reported <br>on 20 June. -- Fabian Schmidt<br><br>COMMUNIST REACTION TO YELTSIN FIRINGS. Communist leader <br>Gennadii Zyuganov on 20 June charged that the arrest of President <br>Yeltsin's two campaign aides was an attempt to stop the second <br>round of the election from taking place, NTV reported. Zyuganov also <br>complained that the firings of Oleg Soskovets, Mikhail Barsukov, and <br>Aleksandr Korzhakov represented "the decapitation of the power <br>structures." Duma Speaker Gennadii Seleznev said that Korzhakov <br>and Barsukov were fired because they "encroached on the holy of <br>holies--the secret financing of the Yeltsin campaign," ITAR-TASS <br>reported on 20 June. Duma Defense Committee Chairman Viktor <br>Ilyukhin argued that the firings were the result of a battle between <br>"mutually exclusive" factions within the president's inner circle. The <br>Communist faction of the Duma also announced that it will demand a <br>detailed report on the events during the night 19-20 June and the <br>reasons for the removal of the three figures. -- Robert Orttung<br><br>CHUBAIS EXPLAINS RECENT EVENTS. Yeltsin campaign adviser <br>Anatolii Chubais said that Korzhakov, Barsukov, and Soskovets <br>decided to arrest Yeltsin campaign aides Sergei Lisovskii and Arkadii <br>Yevstafev because they believed that they were about to lose their <br>own jobs, NTV reported on 20 June. The arrests of the two aides was <br>merely the first step in a plan to discredit Yeltsin's entire campaign <br>headquarters, Chubais claimed. Chubais described the events as the <br>conclusion of a power struggle in the Yeltsin camp between a group <br>that wanted to take power by force and a group that wanted to win <br>the election legitimately, ITAR- TASS reported. He praised the efforts <br>of Lebed in blocking the actions of the hardliners. -- Robert Orttung<br><br>YEVSTAFEV, LISOVSKII DESCRIBE ARREST. "I was arrested at 5 p.m. <br>at the White House by men claiming to represent the president's <br>Security Service," Yevstafev told NTV on 20 June. The men held him <br>until 3 a.m. without explanation and asked numerous questions <br>about the election. Lisovskii said that the box of money allegedly <br>found in his possession was planted, Reuters reported on 20 June. He <br>said that he and Yevstafev had been collecting documents and <br>surveys to prepare for the second round. Lisovskii noted that his <br>interrogators were particularly interested in getting information <br>about the role of Anatolii Chubais. -- Robert Orttung<br><br>KORZHAKOV PLEDGES LOYALTY TO YELTSIN. The former head of <br>Presidential Security Service (SBP), Aleksandr Korzhakov, said on 20 <br>June that he will remain in President Yeltsin's team and "will make <br>every effort to ensure Yeltsin's victory," Russian and Western media <br>reported. Korzhakov blasted Chubais for his critical comments on 20 <br>June, describing him as a "nightmare for Russia." Yeltsin had recently <br>made Korzhakov a minister and "first adviser," and granted broad <br>new powers to the SBP (see OMRI Daily Digest, 23 May 1996). Like <br>Korzhakov, ex-FSB Director Mikhail Barsukov began his career in the <br>9th KGB Directorate and allegedly was Yeltsin's trusted adviser and <br>drinking buddy. According to Izvestiya, Barsukov's son is married to <br>Korzhakov's daughter, and Korzhakov reportedly helped his in-law <br>obtain the position of counterintelligence chief. -- Constantine <br>Dmitriev<br><br>LEBED PRESENTED TO SECURITY COUNCIL. Shortly before firing <br>Korzhakov, Barsukov, and Soskovets, on 20 June President Yeltsin <br>introduced newly- appointed Security Council Secretary Aleksandr <br>Lebed at a Kremlin meeting of the council, Russian media reported. <br>The council, including former Federal Security Service chief Mikhail <br>Barsukov, unanimously endorsed Lebed's appointment. ITAR-TASS <br>reported that Yeltsin charged Lebed "personally" with strengthening <br>the security of society and the individual, as well as insuring political <br>stability. During the meeting, Yeltsin criticized the government for <br>failing to prevent energy companies from cutting off supplies to <br>essential military installations, and blasted the security ministries for <br>"criminal mismanagement" of budget funds, saying that the Defense <br>Ministry had squandered more than 300 billion rubles ($60 million). <br>After the meeting, Lebed said Yeltsin had given him "carte-blanche" <br>to reform the council. -- Scott Parrish<br><br>LEBED SAYS YELTSIN FIRED COUP PLOTTERS. Lebed was greeted "like <br>a national hero" by a crowd that gathered to hear him at a press <br>conference following the Security Council meeting, NTV reported. <br>Lebed declared that Yeltsin had personally decided to fire Barsukov, <br>Korzhakov, and Soskovets after the session. While Yeltsin did not <br>publicly link the sackings with the 19-20 June incident involving the <br>arrest of two Yeltsin campaign staffers, Lebed did. He said an <br>"attempt to pressure the president had been organized," and <br>suggested that the plotters had tried but failed to attract the support <br>of the armed forces. "A certain number of stupid people involved in <br>it will be dismissed," he added. Some observers have suggested that <br>Yeltsin's campaign staff are deliberately exaggerating the danger <br>presented by the recent incident in order to convince voters that <br>Yeltsin and Lebed saved the country from a major crisis. -- Scott <br>Parrish<br><br>NEW RESPONSIBILITIES FOR LOBOV. Oleg Lobov will take over the <br>industrial policy portfolio previously held by sacked First Deputy <br>Prime Minister Oleg Soskovets, Russian and Western agencies <br>reported on 20 June. Soskovets was in charge of the Energy, <br>Transport, Construction, Health, and Nuclear Power ministries, among <br>others. He also supervised various state committees, including those <br>on the defense industry and metallurgy, and chaired the powerful <br>Committee on Operational Questions. Lobov was given the post of <br>first deputy prime minister on 18 June after losing the post of <br>Security Council secretary to make way for Lebed. He is still Yeltsin's <br>special representative in Chechnya but said he will soon relinquish <br>that job. Lobov briefly held the posts of first deputy prime minister <br>and economics minister in 1993; at the time, he called for increased <br>state regulation of the economy and a slowdown in privatization. -- <br>Penny Morvant<br><br>ACTING SECURITY CHIEF NAMED. Following the abrupt dismissal of <br>Barsukov, President Yeltsin on 20 June named a deputy director of <br>the Federal Security Service (FSB), Nikolai Kovalev, as its new acting <br>chief, ITAR- TASS reported. Born in 1949, Kovalev has worked in <br>state security since 1974. He served for two years in Afghanistan <br>and worked in the Moscow and Moscow Oblast branches of the FSB <br>before being made deputy director with responsibility for economic <br>counterintelligence. He was promoted to the rank of colonel general <br>this May. Barsukov served as FSB head for less than a year, taking <br>over from Sergei Stepashin last July in the wake of the Budennovsk <br>hostage crisis. -- Penny Morvant<br><br>NEW BODYGUARD CHIEF FOR YELTSIN. To replace Aleksandr <br>Korzhakov, President Yeltsin signed a decree on 20 June appointing <br>head of the Federal Protection Service (FSO) Lt. Gen. Yurii Krapivin <br>acting chief of the Presidential Security Service (SBP), ITAR-TASS <br>reported. It was the second new title for Krapivin in two days: on 19 <br>June, Yeltsin issued a decree renaming the Main Protection <br>Administration, which Krapivin had headed since 1995, the FSO. That <br>change was mandated by the recently approved law on state <br>protection, which regulates the provision of bodyguards to senior <br>state officials. According to the law, the FSO and the SBP are under <br>the command of the president. Their powers include the right, in <br>relation to their duties, to conduct searches, check identity papers, <br>make arrests, give orders to other state organs, enter premises <br>without the owners' consent, ban access to public places, and recruit <br>and use secret informants. -- Penny Morvant<br><br>IS THE CHECHEN PEACE AGREEMENT UNRAVELLING? Chechen Chief of <br>Staff Aslan Maskhadov on 20 June ordered his forces to refrain from <br>further hostilities until after the second round of the Russian <br>presidential election, reiterating a similar statement of 17 June, <br>ITAR-TASS and Ekho Moskvy reported. Russian Public TV (ORT) <br>quoted the head of the OSCE mission in Grozny, Tim Guldimann, as <br>implying that the implementation of the 10 June peace agreement <br>has been stalled. A meeting between Chechen and Russian military <br>representatives planned for 21 June has been postponed because <br>agreement could not be reached on a venue for it. Each side <br>continues to accuse the other of violating the ceasefire agreement. A <br>Russian armored column is reported to have opened fire on the <br>village of Alkhan-Yurt on 19 June, and 15 Russian troops were killed <br>in the ensuing fighting, according to Ekho Moskvy. On 20 June, a <br>Russian transport helicopter was shot down over the village of <br>Tsentoroi in southeastern Chechnya, killing one person and injuring <br>seven others, AFP reported. -- Liz Fuller<br><br>CENTRAL BANK MAY REVOKE NEW RESERVE REQUIREMENTS. The <br>Central Bank may reverse its 10 June decision to increase mandatory <br>reserves for commercial banks by some 2 trillion rubles ($395 <br>million) (see OMRI Daily Digest, 11 June 1996), ITAR-TASS reported <br>on 20 June. The bank took the step to neutralize the inflationary <br>effect of transferring $1 billion of the bank's profits to the federal <br>budget. However, the increase in reserves has worsened the <br>commercial banks' liquidity problems, already exacerbated by pre-<br>election deposit withdrawals by their customers. The Association of <br>Russian Banks and the Central Bank have agreed to set up a working <br>group to resolve the problem. -- Natalia Gurushina<br><br>FINANCIAL-INDUSTRIAL GROUPS ON INCREASE. The government's <br>Commission on Operational Questions held a meeting on 19 June to <br>discuss the role of financial-industrial groups (FPGs) in the economy, <br>Kommersant-Daily reported. The commission was chaired by First <br>Deputy Prime Minister Oleg Soskovets, who was dismissed the next <br>day. FPGs are voluntary conglomerates of legally independent firms: <br>conservative figures in the government see them as a way of fighting <br>off foreign competition and replacing the coordinating role formerly <br>played by the central ministries. There are currently 34 FPGs, uniting <br>1,457 firms and 49 banks. They account for 10% of GDP, up from 2% <br>a year ago. Despite a presidential decree and a law regulating FPGs, <br>their status remains unclear with respect to tax and investment <br>privileges. Their future is still more uncertain given the removal of <br>Soskovets, their chief sponsor. -- Peter Rutland<br><br>This material  was reprinted with permission of the Open Media   <br>Research Institute,  a nonprofit organization with research offices in   <br>Prague, Czech  Republic. For more information on OMRI publications,   <br>please write to:   info@omri.cz <br>
